question:
Which of the following substances has a property that corresponds to its use?
A. \text{SiO}_2 \text{ has a high hardness and can be used to make optical fibers.}
B. \text{HClO has acidity and can be used as a disinfectant.}
C. \text{SO}_2 \text{ can cause a potassium permanganate solution to fade, indicating that } \text{SO}_2 \text{ has bleaching properties and can be used for bleaching paper.}
D. \text{Iron powder has reducing properties and can be used as a food antioxidant.}

Which of the following statements is correct?
A. \text{KNO}_3, \text{mixed with a small amount of NaCl impurity, can be purified by evaporation crystallization.}
B. \text{Fractional distillation can separate a mixture of carbon tetrachloride and water.}
C. \text{During fractional distillation, the lower layer of liquid is first removed after the liquid stabilizes, then the upper layer is poured out.}
D. \text{SO}_2 \text{, mixed with a small amount of CO}_2 \text{, can be purified by passing through a NaOH solution.}

At room temperature, which of the following ion groups can coexist in large quantities in the specified solution?
A. In a solution with pH=1: \text{Na}^+, \text{Mg}^{2+}, \text{ClO}^-, \text{SO}_4^{2-}
B. In a 0.1mol\cdot L^{-1} \text{BaCl}_2 solution: \text{K}^+, \text{Na}^+, \text{OH}^-, \text{NO}_3^-
C. In a solution containing a large amount of \text{NH}_4^+: \text{Na}^+, \text{K}^+, \text{OH}^-, \text{NO}_3^-
D. In a colorless solution: \text{Fe}^{3+}, \text{K}^+, \text{SCN}^-, \text{SO}_4^{2-}

Among the following substances, which selection of reagents and methods can correctly remove the least amount of impurities?
A. \text{CO}_2(g) + \text{HCl}(g) \quad \text{through} \quad \text{Na}_2\text{CO}_3 \text{solution}
B. \text{NO}_2(g) \quad \text{through} \quad \text{NaOH solution}
C. \text{Na}_2\text{SO}_4(aq) + \text{Na}_2\text{SO}_3(aq) \quad \text{through and heating with} \quad \text{O}_2
D. \text{NaHCO}_3(s) + \text{Na}_2\text{CO}_3(s) \quad \text{through and heating with} \quad \text{O}_2

Which of the following ionic equations is correct?
A. The reaction of \text{CuSO}_4 with dilute H_2S gas: \text{Cu}^{2+} + \text{S}^{2-} = \text{CuS} \downarrow
B. Adding Ba(\text{NO}_3)_2 to \text{H}_2\text{SO}_3 solution: \text{Ba}^{2+} + \text{H}_2\text{SO}_3 = \text{BaSO}_3 \downarrow + 2\text{NO}_3^- + 2 \text{H}^+
C. Passing a small amount of \text{Cl}_2 into \text{NaHCO}_3 solution: \text{Cl}_2 + \text{HCO}_3^- = \text{Cl}^- + \text{ClO}^- + 2\text{CO}_2 \uparrow + \text{H}_2\text{O}
D. Electrolyzing \text{FeCl}_3 solution with a copper plate as a cathode: \text{Cu} + 2\text{Fe}^{3+} = \text{Cu}^{2+} + 2\text{Fe}^{2+}

"Observation and micro-exploration" is one of the scientific literacy elements of chemistry. Which of the following ionic equations is incorrectly represented?
A. The reduction of iron(III) oxide powder is a redox reaction: \, \text{Fe}_2\text{O}_3 + 6\text{H}^+ = 2\text{Fe}^{3+} + 3\text{H}_2\uparrow
B. Adding \text{NaHS} solution to a copper(II) sulfate solution produces a precipitate of black copper sulfide: \, \text{Cu}^{2+} + \text{HS}^- = \text{CuS}\downarrow + \text{H}^+
C. Adding ammonia water to sulfur dioxide results in a reaction: \, \text{SO}_2 + 2\text{OH}^- = \text{SO}_3^{2-} + \text{H}_2\text{O}
D. Adding calcium bicarbonate to lime water results in a formation of precipitate: \, \text{Ca}^{2+} + \text{HCO}_3^- + \text{OH}^- = \text{CaCO}_3\downarrow + \text{H}_2\text{O}

Among the following reactions, which one is an endothermic reaction?
A. \text{Al and dilute } H_2SO_4 \text{ reaction}
B. \text{Na and } C_2H_5OH \text{ reaction}
C. \text{NaOH and } HCl \text{ reaction}
D. \text{Ba(OH)}_2 \cdot 8H_2O \text{ and } NH_4Cl \text{ reaction}

The Earth is surrounded by air. The element with the highest content in the air is
A. \text{O}
B. \text{H}
C. \text{N}
D. \text{C}

Cl_2 can directly react with many single substances to form chlorides. Which of the following compounds is not directly formed from Cl_2 and a single substance?
A. \text{FeCl}_2
B. \text{CuCl}_2
C. \text{HCl}
D. \text{NaCl}

In the aqueous solutions of the following substances, the solute mainly exists in the form of molecules. Which one is it?
A. \text{NH}_3\cdot\text{H}_2\text{O}
B. \text{CH}_3\text{COONa}
C. \text{NaCl}
D. \text{NH}_4\text{Cl}

Among the following transformations, which one is a redox reaction?
A. \ce{SO3 -> H2SO4}
B. \ce{Cu -> CuSO4}
C. \ce{Cl2 -> NaCl}
D. \ce{Fe2O3 -> Fe}

Which of the following transformations cannot be achieved in one step?
A. \text{Na (aq)} \rightarrow \text{Na}_2\text{O} \rightarrow \text{NaOH}
B. \text{S} \rightarrow \text{SO}_2 (g) \rightarrow \text{H}_2\text{SO}_4
C. \text{Fe}_2\text{O}_3 \rightarrow \text{Fe(OH)}_3 \rightarrow \text{FeCl}_3
D. \text{CO}_2 \rightarrow \text{CaCO}_3 \rightarrow \text{CaO (s)}

