D. \text{CO}_2 \rightarrow \text{CaCO}_3 \rightarrow \text{CaO (s)}

Which of the following pairs of substances can directly interconvert?
A. \mathrm{NH_3}, \mathrm{NO}
B. \mathrm{O_2}, \mathrm{F_2}
C. \mathrm{NO}, \mathrm{NO_2}
D. \mathrm{H_2S}, \mathrm{SO_2}

A 500 mL solution contains \( 0.1 \ \text{mol} \ \text{Fe}^{2+} \) and \( 0.2 \ \text{mol} \ \text{Fe}^{3+} \). After adding \( 0.2 \ \text{mol} \) of iron powder and allowing \( \text{Fe}^{3+} \) to be completely reduced, what is the concentration of \( \text{Fe}^{2+} \) in the solution? (Assume the total volume remains unchanged during the reaction.)
A. 0.4 \ \text{mol} \cdot \text{L}^{-1}
B. 0.6 \ \text{mol} \cdot \text{L}^{-1}
C. 0.8 \ \text{mol} \cdot \text{L}^{-1}
D. 1.0 \ \text{mol} \cdot \text{L}^{-1}

Among the following substances, which contains the largest number of nitrogen atoms?
A. 0.1\, \text{mol} \text{NH}_4\text{Cl}
B. 0.1\, \text{mol} \text{NH}_4\text{NO}_3
C. 1.204 \times 10^{23}\, \text{CO(NH}_2\text{)}_2
D. 0.2\, \text{mol} \text{NH}_3\cdot \text{H}_2\text{O}

Among the following ions, which cannot form a coordination compound by reacting with ammonia water?
A. \mathrm{Ag^{+}}
B. \mathrm{Fe^{2+}}
C. \mathrm{Zn^{2+}}
D. \mathrm{Cu^{2+}}

Among the following molecules, which one has a trigonal pyramidal spatial structure?
A. \ce{CS2}
B. \ce{NH3}
C. \ce{CBr4}
D. \ce{C2H6}

Among the following air pollutants, which gas can bind to Fe^{2+} in hemoglobin in human blood through coordination bonds, causing poisoning?
A. SO_{2}
B. CO_{2}
C. NO_{2}
D. CO

Among the following hydrogen-containing compounds, in the liquid state, the one in which intermolecular hydrogen bonds do not exist is
A. \ce{CH4}
B. \ce{NH3}
C. \ce{H2O}
D. \ce{HF}

According to the principle of isoelectronic species, particles composed of elements from the same period can be considered isoelectronic if they have the same total number of electrons, and their physical properties are also similar. Which of the following pairs are isoelectronic species?
A. \ce{O2} and \ce{SO2}
B. \ce{CO} and \ce{N2}
C. \ce{CO} and \ce{NO}
D. \ce{NH4+} and \ce{C2H4}

Which of the following molecules is a linear molecule and all atoms in the molecule have a stable structure satisfying the octet rule?
A. \ce{BeCl2}
B. \ce{C2H2}
C. \ce{CO2}
D. \ce{SO2}

Among the following comparisons of particle radii, which one is correct?
A. \text{Na}^+ > \text{Na}
B. \text{Cl}^- > \text{Cl}
C. \text{Ca}^{2+} > \text{Cl}^-
D. \text{Mg} > \text{Na}

Which of the following substances reacts most violently with water?
A. \mathrm{Li}
B. \mathrm{Na}
C. \mathrm{K}
D. \mathrm{Rb}

Which of the following substances contains an element with a covalent bond?
A. \ce{H2O}
B. \ce{NaCl}
C. \ce{KOH}
D. \ce{Cl2}

Among the following covalent compounds, which has the greatest bond energy?
A. \text{HCl}
B. \text{HF}
C. \text{HBr}
D. \text{HI}

The chemical bonds in a nitrogen molecule \((\text{N}_2)\) are
A. 3 \sigma\text{-bonds}
B. 1 \sigma\text{-bond}, 2 \pi\text{-bonds}
C. 3 \pi\text{-bonds}
D. 1 \sigma\text{-bond}, 1 \pi\text{-bond}

In the following processes, the one where a covalent bond is broken is
A.  \text{Burning sulfur solid in water}
B.  \text{Chlorine gas dissolving in water}
C.  \text{Carbon dioxide turning into dry ice}
D.  \text{Sulfur dissolving in ethanol}

It is known that the mass of \(1.505 \times 10^{23}\) molecules of gas X is 8 grams. What is the molar mass of gas X?
A. 16 g
B. 32 g
C. 64 \text{ g mol}^{-1}
D. 32 \text{ g mol}^{-1}

Under standard conditions, which of the following gases has the largest molar mass?
A. \ce{Cl2}
B. \ce{CH4}
C. \ce{H2}
D. \ce{CO2}

There is an empty bottle with a mass of \( M \) grams. After filling the bottle with air, the total mass is \( M_1 \) grams. Under the same conditions, after filling the bottle with a certain gas, the total mass is \( M_2 \) grams. What is the molar mass of this gas?
A. \left[ \frac{M_1 - M}{M_2 - M} \right] \times 29
B. \left[ \frac{M_2 - M}{M_1 - M} \right] \times 29 \text{ g/mol}
C. \left[ \frac{M_2 - M}{M_1 - M} - M \right] \times 29
D. \left[ \frac{M_1 - M}{M_2 - M} \right] \times 29 \text{ g/mol}

The molar mass of \( \text{CO}_2 \) is
A. 44
B. 44 \text{g}
C. 44 \text{g/mol}
D. 44 \text{mol}

In the raw materials for making glass, adding which of the following substances can produce blue glass?
A. Cu_{2}O
B. CoO
C. Al_{2}O_{3}
D. SiO_{2}

Which of the following reactions involves nitrogen fixation?
A. ① \text{N and H react under certain conditions to form } \text{NH}_3
B. ② \text{N and O in the air react to form } \text{NO} \text{ during thunderstorms}
C. ③ \text{NH}_3 \text{ is oxidized to form } \text{NO}
D. ④ \text{NH}_3 \text{ and } \text{HNO}_3 \text{ react to form } \text{NH}_4\text{NO}_3

Which of the following substances cannot react with sodium hydroxide solution?
A. \text{Mg}
B. \text{Al(OH)}_3
C. \text{Al}
D. \text{CO}_2

Red coral grows in sea areas with depths of 200 to 2000 meters, such as the Taiwan Strait and the South China Sea. It is regarded as an organic gemstone along with amber and pearls. In China, coral symbolizes auspiciousness and wealth and has been used to make precious handicrafts for a long time. Red coral is a dry branch-like material formed by the accumulation of the calcareous skeletons of countless coral insects. Its red color is due to the long-term accumulation of a certain element on the seabed. What is this element?
A. \ce{Na}
B. \ce{Fe}
C. \ce{Si}
D. \ce{Cu}

Among the following metal oxides, which one belongs to amphoteric oxides?
A. \mathrm{Na_2O_2}
B. \mathrm{Al_2O_3}
C. \mathrm{Fe_2O_3}
D. \mathrm{CaO}

Red coral is a branch-like object formed by the accumulation of large amounts of limestone from countless coral polyps. Its red color is due to the long-term accumulation of a certain element's compounds on the seabed. Which element is this?
A. \text{Na}
B. \text{Fe}
C. \text{Si}
D. \text{Cu}

The red coral produced in the Taiwan Strait is a symbol of good fortune in China and has always been used to make precious handicrafts. Analysis shows that its red color is due to the oxide of a certain element. Try to infer this element.
A. \text{Na}
B. \text{Mg}
C. \text{Fe}
D. \text{Ca}

To test whether a certain \( \text{FeCl}_2 \) solution has deteriorated, which of the following can be added to the solution?
A. \text{NaOH solution}
B. Iron pieces
C. \text{KSCN solution}
D. Starch solution

The Beijing 2008 Olympic gold medals are made of gold discs with a diameter of 70 mm and a thickness of 6 mm. A chemistry interest group speculated about the metal composition of the medals: Person A believed that the metal was made of pure gold; Person B believed that the metal was made of a gold-silver alloy; Person C believed that the metal was made of brass (a copper-zinc alloy). To verify their speculations, a small amount of the material powder from the medal was taken for an experiment. Which of the following reagents should be added to prove their speculations wrong?
A. \text{A. Copper sulfate solution}
B. \text{B. Hydrochloric acid}
C. \text{C. Dilute nitric acid}
D. \text{D. Silver nitrate solution}

Sodium chloride, aluminum chloride, ferrous chloride, cobalt chloride, and potassium thiocyanate solutions can be distinguished by a simple experiment using only one reagent. What is this reagent?
A. \mathrm{KSCN}
B. \mathrm{BaCl_2}
C. \mathrm{NaOH}
D. \mathrm{HCl}

A substance R in river water reacts with oxygen, and the chemical equation for the reaction is \(2R + 2H_2O + 7O_2 = 2FeSO_4 + 2H_2SO_4\). What is the chemical formula of R?
A. \text{FeS}
B. \text{FeS}_2
C. \text{FeO}
D. \text{Fe}_2\text{S}_3

The carbon dioxide produced by the breathing of submarine crew members can react chemically with \(2 \text{Na}_2\text{O}_2 + 2 \text{CO}_2 = 2X + \text{O}_2\) to absorb \(\text{O}_2\). What is the chemical formula of \(X\)?
A. \text{NaOH}
B. \text{Na}_2\text{C}
C. \text{Na}_2\text{CO}_2
D. \text{Na}_2\text{CO}_3

Which reagent can distinguish between \( \text{NH}_4\text{Cl} \), \( \text{K}_2\text{SO}_4 \), \( \text{NaCl} \), and \( (\text{NH}_4)_2\text{SO}_4 \) among the four colorless solutions?
A. Ba\left(\text{NO}_3\right)_2 \text{ solution}
B. Ba\left(\text{OH}\right)_2 \text{ solution}
C. Ag\text{NO}_3 \text{ solution}
D. \text{NaOH solution}
